This documentation provides guidelines on setting up and using the RESTful API for managing blog posts.

//** Setup **//
Installation

Before using the API, ensure you have Node.js and npm installed on your system. Then, follow these steps:
    npm install express mongoose bootstrap cors 


//** Project Structure **//

    RESTFUL API/
├── Backend/
│  └── controllers/
│       └── BlogControllers.js
│  └── models/
│       └── BlogModels.js
│  └──routing/
│       └── BlogRouting.js   
├── app.js



//** Usage **//
Now, you can use the following endpoints to interact with the API:

[1] Add a Post
URL:/posts/addPost
Method: POST
Request Body: JSON object containing post data (title, content, author, creation date)

[2] Update a Post
URL: /posts/update/:id
Method: PUT
Request Parameters: Post ID
Request Body: JSON object containing post data to update (title, content, author)

[3]Delete a Post
URL: /posts/delete/:id
Method: DELETE
Request Parameters: Post ID

[4]Show All Posts
URL: /posts/showAll
Method: GET

[5]Find a Post by ID
URL: /posts/show/:id
Method: GET
Request Parameters: Post ID
